==Algebra==
===Convert to interval notation===
{{question-answer|question= 1. <math> \{x:-4<x<2\} \, </math>|answer={{noprint|<math>(-4,2)</math>}}}}
{{question-answer|question= 2. <math> \{x:-\frac{7}{3} \leq x \leq -\frac{1}{3}\} </math>|answer={{noprint|<math>[-\frac{7}{3},-\frac{1}{3}]</math>}}}}
{{question-answer|question= 3. <math> \{x:-\pi \leq x < \pi\} </math>|answer={{noprint|<math>[-\pi,\pi)</math>}}}}
{{question-answer|question= 4. <math> \{x:x \leq \frac{17}{9}\} </math>|answer={{noprint|<math>(-\infty, \frac{17}{9}]</math>}}}}
{{question-answer|question= 5. <math> \{x:5 \leq x+1 \leq 6\} </math>|answer={{noprint|<math>[4, 5]</math>}}}}
{{question-answer|question= 6. <math> \{x:x - \frac{1}{4} < 1\} \, </math>|answer={{noprint|<math>(-\infty, \frac{5}{4})</math>}}}}
{{question-answer|question= 7. <math> \{x:3 > 3x\} \,</math>|answer={{noprint|<math>(-\infty, 1)</math>}}}}
{{question-answer|question= 8. <math> \{x:0 \leq 2x+1 < 3\} </math>|answer={{noprint|<math>[-\frac{1}{2}, 1)</math>}}}}
{{question-answer|question= 9. <math> \{x:5<x \mbox{ and } x<6\} \, </math>|answer={{noprint|<math>(5,6)</math>}}}}
{{question-answer|question=10. <math> \{x:5<x \mbox{ or } x<6\} \, </math>|answer={{noprint|<math>(-\infty,\infty)</math>}}}}

===State the following intervals using set notation===
{{question-answer|question=11. <math> [3,4] \, </math>|answer={{noprint|<math>\{x:3\leq x\leq 4\}</math>}}}}
{{question-answer|question=12. <math> [3,4) \, </math>|answer={{noprint|<math>\{x:3\leq x<4\}</math>}}}}
{{question-answer|question=13. <math> (3,\infty) </math>|answer={{noprint|<math>\{x:x>3\}</math>}}}}
{{question-answer|question=14. <math> (-\frac{1}{3}, \frac{1}{3}) \, </math>|answer={{noprint|<math>\{x:-\frac{1}{3}<x<\frac{1}{3}\}</math>}}}}
{{question-answer|question=15. <math> (-\pi, \frac{15}{16}) \, </math>|answer={{noprint|<math>\{x:-\pi<x<\frac{15}{16}\}</math>}}}}
{{question-answer|question=16. <math> (-\infty,\infty) </math>|answer={{noprint|<math>\{x:x\in\Re\}</math>}}}}

===Which one of the following is a true statement?===
Hint: the true statement is often referred to as the ''triangle inequality.''  Give examples where the other two are false.
{{question-answer|question=17. <math> |x+y| = |x| + |y| \, </math>|answer={{noprint|false}}}}
{{question-answer|question=18. <math> |x+y| \geq |x| + |y| </math>|answer={{noprint|false}}}}
{{question-answer|question=19. <math> |x+y| \leq |x| + |y| </math>|answer={{noprint|true}}}}

===Evaluate the following expressions===
{{question-answer|question=20. <math> 8^{1/3} \, </math>|answer={{noprint|<math>2</math>}}}}
{{question-answer|question=21. <math> (-8)^{1/3} \, </math>|answer={{noprint|<math>-2</math>}}}}
{{question-answer|question=22. <math> \bigg(\frac{1}{8}\bigg)^{1/3} \, </math>|answer={{noprint|<math>\frac{1}{2}</math>}}}}
{{question-answer|question=23. <math> (8^{2/3}) (8^{3/2}) (8^0) \, </math>|answer={{noprint|<math>8^{13/6}</math>}}}}
{{question-answer|question=24. <math> \bigg( \bigg(\frac{1}{8}\bigg)^{1/3} \bigg)^7 </math>|answer={{noprint|<math>\frac{1}{128}</math>}}}}
{{question-answer|question=25. <math> \sqrt[3]{\frac{27}{8}} </math>|answer={{noprint|<math>\frac{3}{2}</math>}}}}
{{question-answer|question=26. <math> \frac{4^5 \cdot 4^{-2}}{4^3} </math>|answer={{noprint|<math>1</math>}}}}
{{question-answer|question=27. <math> \bigg(\sqrt{27}\bigg)^{2/3} </math>|answer={{noprint|<math>3</math>}}}}
{{question-answer|question=28. <math> \frac{\sqrt{27}}{\sqrt[3]{9}} </math>|answer={{noprint|<math>3^{5/6}</math>}}}}

===Simplify the following===
{{question-answer|question=29. <math> x^3 + 3x^3 \, </math>|answer={{noprint|<math>4x^3</math>}}}}
{{question-answer|question=30. <math> \frac{x^3 + 3x^3}{x^2} </math>|answer={{noprint|<math>4x</math>}}}}
{{question-answer|question=31. <math> (x^3+3x^3)^3 \, </math>|answer={{noprint|<math>64x^9</math>}}}}
{{question-answer|question=32. <math> \frac{x^{15} + x^3}{x} </math>|answer={{noprint|<math>x^{14}+x^2</math>}}}}
{{question-answer|question=33. <math> (2x^2)(3x^{-2}) \, </math>|answer={{noprint|<math>6</math>}}}}
{{question-answer|question=34. <math> \frac{x^2y^{-3}}{x^3y^2} </math>|answer={{noprint|<math>\frac{1}{xy^5}</math>}}}}
{{question-answer|question=35. <math> \sqrt{x^2y^4} </math>|answer={{noprint|<math>|xy^2|</math>}}}}
{{question-answer|question=36. <math> \bigg(\frac{8x^6}{y^4}\bigg)^{1/3} </math>|answer={{noprint|<math>\frac{2x^2}{y^{4/3}}</math>}}}}

===Find the roots of the following polynomials===
{{question-answer|question=37. <math> x^2 - 1 \, </math>|answer={{noprint|<math>x=\pm1</math>}}}}
{{question-answer|question=38. <math> x^2 +2x +1 \, </math>|answer={{noprint|<math>x=-1</math>}}}}
{{question-answer|question=39. <math> x^2 + 7x + 12 \, </math>|answer={{noprint|<math>x=-3, x=-4</math>}}}}
{{question-answer|question=40. <math> 3x^2 - 5x -2 \, </math>|answer={{noprint|<math>x=2, x=-\frac{1}{3}</math>}}}}
{{question-answer|question=41. <math> x^2 + 5/6x + 1/6 \, </math>|answer={{noprint|<math>x=-\frac{1}{3}, x=-\frac{1}{2}</math>}}}}
{{question-answer|question=42. <math> 4x^3 + 4x^2 + x \, </math>|answer={{noprint|<math>x=0,x=-\frac{1}{2}</math>}}}}
{{question-answer|question=43. <math> x^4 - 1 \, </math>|answer={{noprint|<math>x=\pm i, x=\pm 1</math>}}}}
{{question-answer|question=44. <math> x^3 + 2x^2 - 4x - 8 \, </math>|answer={{noprint|<math>x=\pm2</math>}}}}

===Factor the following expressions===
{{question-answer|question=45. <math> 4a^2 - ab - 3b^2 \, </math>|answer={{noprint|<math>(4a+3b)(a-b)</math>}}}}
{{question-answer|question=46. <math> (c+d)^2 - 4 \, </math>|answer={{noprint|<math>(c+d+2)(c+d-2)</math>}}}}
{{question-answer|question=47. <math> 4x^2 - 9y^2 \, </math>|answer={{noprint|<math>(2x+3y)(2x-3y)</math>}}}}

===Simplify the following===
{{question-answer|question=48. <math> \frac{x^2 -1}{x+1} \, </math>|answer={{noprint|<math>x-1, x\neq-1</math>}}}}
{{question-answer|question=49. <math> \frac{3x^2 + 4x + 1}{x+1} \, </math>|answer={{noprint|<math>3x+1, x\neq-1</math>}}}}
{{question-answer|question=50. <math> \frac{4x^2 - 9}{4x^2 + 12x + 9} \, </math>|answer={{noprint|<math>\frac{2x-3}{2x+3}</math>}}}}
{{question-answer|question=51. <math> \frac{x^2 + y^2 +2xy}{x(x+y)} \, </math>|answer={{noprint|<math>\frac{x+y}{x}, x\neq-y</math>}}}}

==Functions==

52. Let <math>f(x)=x^2</math>.
{{question-answer|question=a. Compute <math>f(0)</math>, <math>f(2)</math>, and <math>f(-1.2)</math>.|answer={{noprint|<math>f(0)=0</math>, <math>f(2)=4</math>, and <math>f(-1.2)=1.44</math>}}}}
{{question-answer|question=b. What are the domain and range of <math>f</math>?|answer={{noprint|Domain is <math>{(-\infty,\infty)}</math>; range is <math>[0,\infty)</math>}}}}
{{question-answer|question=c. Does <math>f</math> have an inverse? If so, find a formula for it.|answer={{noprint|No, <math>f</math> is not one-to-one. For example, both <math>x=1</math> and <math>x=-1</math> result in <math>f(x)=1</math>.}}}}

53. Let <math>f(x)=x+2</math>, <math>g(x)=1/x</math>.<br/>
:a. Give formulae for
{{question-answer|question=i. <math>f+g</math>|answer={{noprint|<math>(f + g)(x) = x + 2 + \frac{1}{x}</math>}}}}
{{question-answer|question=ii. <math>f-g</math>|answer={{noprint|<math>(f - g)(x) = x + 2 - \frac{1}{x}</math>}}}}
{{question-answer|question=iii. <math>g-f</math>|answer={{noprint|<math>(g - f)(x) = \frac{1}{x} - x - 2</math>}}}}
{{question-answer|question=iv. <math>f\times g</math>|answer={{noprint|<math>(f \times g)(x) = 1 + \frac{2}{x}</math>}}}}
{{question-answer|question=v. <math>f/g</math>|answer={{noprint|<math>(f / g)(x) = x^2 + 2x</math>}}}}
{{question-answer|question=vi. <math>g/f</math>|answer={{noprint|<math>(g / f)(x) = \frac{1}{x^2 + 2x}</math>}}}}
{{question-answer|question=vii. <math>f\circ g</math>|answer={{noprint|<math>(f \circ g)(x) = \frac{1}{x} + 2</math>}}}}
{{question-answer|question=viii. <math>g\circ f</math>|answer={{noprint|<math>(g \circ f)(x) = \frac{1}{x + 2}</math>}}}}
{{question-answer|question=b. Compute <math>f(g(2))</math> and <math>g(f(2))</math>.|answer={{noprint|<math>f(g(2))=5/2, g(f(2))=1/4</math>|}}}}
{{question-answer|question=c. Do <math>f</math> and <math>g</math> have inverses? If so, find formulae for them.|answer={{noprint|<math>f^{-1}(x)=x-2, g^{-1}(x)=\frac{1}{x}</math>}}}}

{{question-answer|question=54. Does this graph represent a function? [[Image:Sinx over x.svg]]|answer={{noprint|Yes.}}}}

55. Consider the following function 
:<math>f(x) = \begin{cases} -\frac{1}{9} & \mbox{if } x<-1 \\ 2 & \mbox{if } -1\leq x \leq 0 \\ x + 3 & \mbox{if } x>0. \end{cases} </math>
{{question-answer|question=a. What is the domain?|answer={{noprint|<math>{(-\infty,\infty)}</math>}}}}
{{question-answer|question=b. What is the range?|answer={{noprint|<math>{(-1/9,\infty)}</math>}}}}
{{question-answer|question=c. Where is <math>f</math> continuous?|answer={{noprint|<math>{x>0}</math>}}}}

56. Consider the following function 
:<math>f(x) = \begin{cases} x^2 & \mbox{if } x>0 \\ -1 & \mbox{if } x\leq 0. \end{cases} </math>
{{question-answer|question=a. What is the domain?|answer={{noprint|<math>{(-\infty,\infty)}</math>}}}}
{{question-answer|question=b. What is the range?|answer={{noprint|<math>{(-1, \infty)}</math>}}}}
{{question-answer|question=c. Where is <math>f</math> continuous?|answer={{noprint|<math>{x>0}</math>}}}}

57. Consider the following function 
:<math>f(x) = \frac{\sqrt{2x-3}}{x-10} </math>
{{question-answer|question=a. What is the domain?|answer={{noprint|<math>{(3/2,10) \cup (10,\infty)}</math>}}}}
{{question-answer|question=b. What is the range?|answer={{noprint|<math>{(-\infty,\infty)}</math>}}}}
{{question-answer|question=c. Where is <math>f</math> continuous?|answer={{noprint|<math>{(3/2,10) and (x>10)}</math>}}}}

58. Consider the following function 
:<math>f(x) = \frac{x-7}{x^2-49} </math>
{{question-answer|question=a. What is the domain?|answer={{noprint|<math>{(-\infty,-7) \cup (-7,\infty)}</math>}}}}
{{question-answer|question=b. What is the range?|answer={{noprint|<math>{(-\infty,\infty)}</math>}}}}
{{question-answer|question=c. Where is <math>f</math> continuous?|answer={{noprint|<math>{(-\infty,-7) and (-7,\infty)}</math>}}}}

