==Convert to interval notation==
{{question-answer|question=1. <math> \{x:-4<x<2\} \, </math>|answer=<math>\mathbf{(-4,2)}</math>}}

{{question-answer|question=2. <math> \{x:-\frac{7}{3} \leq x \leq -\frac{1}{3}\} </math>|answer=<math>\mathbf{[-\frac{7}{3},-\frac{1}{3}]}</math>}}

{{question-answer|question=3. <math> \{x:-\pi \leq x < \pi\} </math>|answer=<math>\mathbf{[-\pi,\pi)}</math>}}

{{question-answer|question=4. <math> \{x:x \leq 17/9\} </math>|answer=<math>\mathbf{(-\infty, \frac{17}{9}]}</math>}}

{{question-answer|question=5. <math> \{x:5 \leq x+1 \leq 6\} </math>|answer=
<math>4\leq x\leq5</math><br/>
<math>\mathbf{[4, 5]}</math>}}

{{question-answer|question=6. <math> \{x:x - 1/4 < 1\} \, </math>|answer=
<math>x<1 \frac{1}{4}=\frac{5}{4}</math><br/>
<math>\mathbf{(-\infty, \frac{5}{4})}</math>}}

{{question-answer|question=7. <math> \{x:3 > 3x\} \,</math>|answer=
<math>1>x</math><br/>
<math>x<1</math><br/>
<math>\mathbf{(-\infty, 1)}</math>}}

{{question-answer|question=8. <math> \{x:0 \leq 2x+1 < 3\} </math>|answer=
<math>-1\leq 2x\leq 2</math><br/>
<math>-\frac{1}{2}\leq x<1</math><br/>
<math>\mathbf{[-\frac{1}{2}, 1)}</math>}}

{{question-answer|question=9. <math> \{x:5<x \mbox{ and } x<6\} \, </math>|answer=
This is equivalent to <math>5<x<6</math><br/>
<math>\mathbf{(5,6)}</math>}}

{{question-answer|question=10. <math> \{x:5<x \mbox{ or } x<6\} \, </math>|answer=
It helps to draw a picture to determine the set of numbers described:<br/>
:[[file:5_lt_x_or_x_lt_6.png]]<br/>
A number in the set can be on either the red or blue line, so the entire number line is included.<br/>
<math>\mathbf{(-\infty,\infty)}</math>}}

==State the following intervals using set notation==
{{question-answer|question=11. <math> [3,4] \, </math>|answer=
<math>\mathbf{\{x:3\leq x\leq 4\}}</math>}}

{{question-answer|question=12. <math> [3,4) \, </math>|answer=
<math>\mathbf{\{x:3\leq x<4\}}</math>}}

{{question-answer|question=13. <math> (3,\infty) </math>|answer=
<math>\mathbf{\{x:x>3\}}</math>}}

{{question-answer|question=14. <math> (-\frac{1}{3}, \frac{1}{3}) \, </math>|answer=
<math>\mathbf{\{x:-\frac{1}{3}<x<\frac{1}{3}\}}</math>}}

{{question-answer|question=15. <math> (-\pi, \frac{15}{16}) \, </math>|answer=
<math>\mathbf{\{x:-\pi<x<\frac{15}{16}\}}</math>}}

{{question-answer|question=16. <math> (-\infty,\infty) </math>|answer=
<math>\mathbf{\{x:x\in\Re\}}</math>}}

==Which one of the following is a true statement?==
{{question-answer|question=17. <math> |x+y| = |x| + |y| \, </math>|answer=
Let <math>x=-5, y=5</math>.  Then<br/>
<math>|x+y|=|-5+5|=|0|=0</math>, and<br/>
<math>|x|+|y|=|-5|+|5|=5+5=10</math><br/>
Thus, <math>|x+y| \neq |x| + |y|</math><br/>
'''false'''}}

{{question-answer|question=18. <math> |x+y| \geq |x| + |y| </math>|answer=
Using the same example as above, we have <math>|x+y|\ngeq |x| + |y|</math>.<br/>
'''false'''}}

{{question-answer|question=19. <math> |x+y| \leq |x| + |y| </math>|answer=
'''true'''}}

==Evaluate the following expressions==
{{question-answer|question=20. <math> 8^{1/3} \, </math>|answer=
<math>(2^3)^{1/3}=2^1=\mathbf{2}</math>}}

{{question-answer|question=21. <math> (-8)^{1/3} \, </math>|answer=
<math>(-2^3)^{1/3}=-2^1=\mathbf{-2}</math>}}

{{question-answer|question=22. <math> \bigg(\frac{1}{8}\bigg)^{1/3} \, </math>|answer=
<math>(\frac{1}{2^3})^{1/3}=(2^{-3})^{1/3}=2^{-1}=\mathbf{\frac{1}{2}}</math>}}

{{question-answer|question=23. <math> (8^{2/3}) (8^{3/2}) (8^0) \, </math>|answer=
<math>8^{\frac{2}{3}+\frac{3}{2}+0}=8^{\frac{4}{6}+\frac{9}{6}}=8^{\frac{13}{6}}=(2^3)^{\frac{13}{6}}=\mathbf{2^{13/2}}</math>}}

{{question-answer|question=24. <math> \bigg( \bigg(\frac{1}{8}\bigg)^{1/3} \bigg)^7 </math>|answer=
<math>((\frac{1}{2^3})^{1/3})^7=((2^{-3})^{1/3})^7=(2^{-1})^7=2^{-7}=\frac{1}{2^7}=\mathbf{\frac{1}{128}}</math>}}

{{question-answer|question=25. <math> \sqrt[3]{\frac{27}{8}} </math>|answer=
<math>(\frac{27}{8})^{1/3}=(\frac{3^3}{2^3})^{1/3}=\frac{3^1}{2^1}=\mathbf{\frac{3}{2}}</math>}}

{{question-answer|question=26. <math> \frac{4^5 \cdot 4^{-2}}{4^3} </math>|answer=
<math>4^{5-2-3}=4^0=\mathbf{1}</math>}}

{{question-answer|question=27. <math> \bigg(\sqrt{27}\bigg)^{2/3} </math>|answer=
<math>((3^3)^{1/2})^{2/3}=(3^\frac{3}{2})^\frac{2}{3}=3^1=\mathbf{3}</math>}}

{{question-answer|question=28. <math> \frac{\sqrt{27}}{\sqrt[3]{9}} </math>|answer=
<math>\frac{(3^3)^{1/2}}{(3^2)^{1/3}}=\frac{3^\frac{3}{2}}{3^\frac{2}{3}}=3^{\frac{3}{2}-\frac{2}{3}}=3^{\frac{9}{6}-\frac{4}{6}}=\mathbf{3^{5/6}}</math>}}

==Simplify the following==
